\faauto\ls17\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 That a taste for fruit is inherent in man is an opinion which is sanctioned by the
 conduct of man in all ages and in all countries.  While some nations have considered it profanation or pollution to nourish themselves with flesh or solace themselves with fish, while almost every member of the animal creation has in turn been considered
 
either sacred or unclean, mankind, in all climes and in all countries, the Hindoo and the Hebrew, the Egyptian and the Greek, the Roman and the Frank, have, in some degree, made good their boastful claim to reason, by universally feeding upon those deligh
tful productions of Nature which are nourished with the dews of heaven, and which live for ever in its breath.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx900{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 
