\faauto\ls20\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 In the meantime, the public agitation was subsiding.  The nation reconciled itself to the revolution in its fortunes.  The }{\i\f1\cgrid0 ci-devant}{\f1\cgrid0 
 millionaires were busied with retrenchment; the Government engaged in sweeping in as many pink shells as were lying about the country; the mechanics contrived to live upon chalk and sea-weed; and as the Aboriginal would not give hi
s corn away gratis, the Vraibleusians determined to give up bread.  The intellectual part of the nation were intently interested in discovering the cause of the National Distress.  One of the philosophers said that it might all be traced to the effects of
 
a war in which the Vraibleusians had engaged about a century before.  Another showed that it was altogether clearly ascribable to the pernicious custom of issuing pink shells; but if, instead of this mode of representing wealth, they had had recourse to b
