\faauto\ls21\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 The indictment was read.  He listened to it with intense attention.  To his surprise, he fo
und himself accused of stealing two hundred and nineteen Camelopards.  All was now explained.  He perceived that he had been mistaken the whole of this time for another person.  He could not contain himself.  He burst into an exclamation.  He told the jud
g
e, in a voice of mingled delight, humility, and triumph, that it was possible he might be guilty of high treason, because he was ignorant of what the crime consisted; but as for stealing two hundred and nineteen Camelopards, he declared that such a larcen
y was a moral impossibility, because he had never seen one such animal in the whole course of his life.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx900{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 
