\faauto\ls21\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 The judge was kind and considerate.  He told the prisoner that the charge of stealing Camelopards was a fiction of law; that he had no doubt h
e had never seen one in the whole course of his life, nor in all probability had any one in the whole Court.  He explained to Popanilla, that originally this animal greatly abounded in Vraibleusia; that the present Court, the highest and most ancient in t
h
e kingdom, had then been instituted for tile punishment of all those who molested or injured that splendid animal.  The species, his lordship continued, had been long extinct; but the Vraibleusians, duly reverencing the institutions of their ancestors, ha
d
 never presumed to abrogate the authority of the Camelopard Court, or invest any other with equal privileges.  Therefore, his lordship added, in order to try you in this Court for a modern offence of high treason, you must first be introduced by fiction o
f law as a stealer of Camelopards, and then being }{\i\f1\cgrid0 in pr\'e6senti regio}{\f1\cgrid0 
, in a manner, we proceed to business by a special power for the absolute offence.  Popanilla was so confounded by the kindness of the judge and the clearness of his lordship's statement that he quite lost the thread of his peroration.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx900{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\cgrid0 
